Here is an optimized algorithm in Python that reverses a given string with minimal memory usage and maximal time efficiency:
```python
def reverse_string(s):
    if not s:
        return s
    return s[-1] + reverse_string(s[:-1])
```
This algorithm uses recursion to reverse the string. It checks if the input string is empty, and if so, it returns the empty string. Otherwise, it returns the last character of the string concatenated with the result of calling the function recursively on the substring that excludes the last character.
This algorithm has a time complexity of O(n), where n is the length of the input string, and a space complexity of O(n), which is minimal for a recursive algorithm.
